Website Fingerprinting Tool


Overview

This directory contains all Python scripts necessary for performing website fingerprinting attacks. The setup requires two virtual machines and an additional host machine.


Requirements

The environment setup is the same as the previous tools, requiring:

Ubuntu 20 as the attacker's virtual machine

Windows 11 (4K display) as the victim's virtual machine (accessed via RDP)

GCC: gcc-11.4

CUDA: CUDA 12.6

Vulkan: Vulkan 1.2.131


Included Files

The folder contains the following scripts and binaries:

dummy.cu

dummy

get-position.py

web-attacker.py

web-victim.py


Setup and Execution

Step 1: Configure the Attacker Virtual Machine (Ubuntu 20)

Place web-attacker.py, dummy, and the prime_probe binary (generated from the Prime Probe Tool) in the attacker's VM directory.

Ensure the system meets the Ubuntu 20 requirements.

Step 2: Configure the Victim Machine (Windows 11)

Open Microsoft Edge and set the homepage to about:blank.

Run Remote Desktop Protocol (RDP) to connect from the host machine to the Windows 11 virtual machine.

Place web-victim.py on the host machine.

Step 3: Running the Attack

On the host machine, run:

python3 web-victim.py

On the attacker's virtual machine, run:

python3 web-attacker.py


Adjusting Mouse Position

If the automation is not precise enough, run get-position.py to reconfigure mouse positioning and ensure proper execution of the scripts.


